7 years ago there was an article about [Bittorrent over Tor isn't a good idea](https://blog.torproject.org/blog/bittorrent-over-tor-isnt-good-idea), but ZeroNet only using BitTorrent for peer discovery, the transfer protocol is different and should not leak your ip as it described in this blogpost and nowdays the Tor network [can handle much more traffic](https://metrics.torproject.org/bandwidth.html?start=2010-01-09&end=2017-04-09), than back then.
I think the goals are the same, and everyone want to avoid situations like this: [An Anonymous group just took down a fifth of the dark web
](http://www.theverge.com/2017/2/3/14497992/freedom-hosting-ii-hacked-anonymous-dark-web-tor)
